Here's the approach for runtime theme switching in .NET MAUI:

## 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextPrimary">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#0078D4</Color>
    <!-- ... -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create similar files for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` using the same keys but different values.

## 2. Merge a default theme in `App.xaml`

```xml
<Application.Resources>
    <ResourceDictionary>
        <ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
            <local:LightTheme />
        </ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
    </ResourceDictionary>
</Application.Resources>
```

## 3. Create a theme-switching service

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static void LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        if (Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme))
            ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

## 4. Call on startup (`App.xaml.cs`)

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.LoadSavedTheme();
}
```

## 5. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var selected = (ThemeService.AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

## Key points

- Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) in your XAML so controls update immediately when the dictionary swaps:
  ```xml
  <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource TextPrimary}" />
  ```
- Keep the same keys across all three dictionaries — only values differ.
- `MergedDictionaries.Clear()` + re-add triggers the dynamic resource refresh app-wide with no restart needed.
